setLockPeriod(uint256,uint256).details: Only owner of the contract can call this function

stakeEther(uint256).details: the wethGatewayAddress interface take the funds from the contract and deposit to AaveV3aWeth tokens are generated and balance is updated as aWeth tokens to keep track of the position

withdrawPosition(uint256).details: First the WETH will be withdrawn from AaveV3 to the contract and then transfer to the user as ETHwethGatewayAddress needs to be approved to burn the aWeth tokens

params._positionId: The positionId of the position created by the user

setLockPeriod(uint256,uint256).notice: Function to allow owner of the contract to change lockPeriods

stakeEther(uint256).notice: Function to allow user to deposit ETH funds to the contractPosition is created after the user deposits ETH to AaveV3positionId is pushed to the s_positionIdsByAddress mapping to keep track of all position

withdrawPosition(uint256).notice: Function to allow user to unstake ETH funds from the contract and earn interestThe function can only be called by the user who created the positionIf the user unstake before unlockDate, the user will not earn interestThe user then receives the ETH and the position is closed
